Log Cabin Prefab

Made by The Giblets of Jesus


Info

This is my entry for The Christmas Triple-Design Contest.
Well, somebody had to break the ice, I thought it might as well be the one to start.

I might make something a little better should anything come to mind, but I think that this will do for now.

Each skin is made form the same brushwork but with different textures assigned to them. Each prefab is also a wooden physbox which breaks only on trigger (Might want to turn that flag off, depends on what you use it for) and has a texture scale of 0.125 for extra detail.

Additional info

The props and skybox seen in the screenshots are Moroes pine trees, this foliage pack from Garrysmod.org and the frozen skybox texture made by Komaokc.

If you do decide to use this prefab in one of your maps, I'd like to be credited as appropriate and while not required, it'd be nice to told so I could see how people have used it.

Need another winter prefab? Check out my Log Cabin Prefab!
